# Proper Testing

When code changes require tests:

## Do

- Write tests in `tests/` directory
- Follow existing test structure
- Use pytest conventions
- Name files `test_*.py`
- Name functions `test_*`

## Do Not

- Create adhoc test scripts in project root
- Write temporary `check_*.py` files
- Create `verify_*.py` throwaway scripts
- Add test code to `if __name__ == "__main__"` blocks

## Test Location

```
tests/
  test_<module>.py      # Unit tests
  test_integration.py   # Integration tests
  conftest.py           # Shared fixtures
```

## Example

```python
# tests/test_codec.py
import pytest
from ib_interface.protobuf.codec import ProtobufCodec

def test_encode_decode_roundtrip():
    # Test implementation
    pass
```
